snippet.title: RISKY crossing  #automobile  #shorts  #short cred via IG@hiveandvine_holistic
snippet.description:
This man decided to take a risk. Because of the flood, the crossing was submerged, and the water had risen to its level.
The current was so strong that it swept away everything in its path.

The driver decided to attempt the water crossing, knowing that in just a few hours he would be cut off from the other bank, where his family was waiting.
As he started moving forward, the stream began to push the light sedan aside, pressing it toward the edge of the crossing.

Unfortunately, there were still several hundred meters left to the other end, and the chances of the car making it across were getting slimmer and slimmer.
In such a situation, the driver‚Äôs task is to hold the wheel tightly, constantly correcting the course. He must not brake sharply, accelerate aggressively, or make sudden maneuvers.

Finally, as the car was almost reaching the shore, it startled two seagulls‚Äîand then successfully drove up onto the bank.

snippet.title: XEV 9e Uses Advanced Noise Cancellation To Block All Sound From Outside The Vehicle üîä #automobile
snippet.description:
The Mahindra XEV 9e promises a cabin so quiet it feels like the outside world disappears.

Marketing claims suggest "advanced noise cancellation" that blocks all external sound.

In reality, the SUV doesn't use traditional active noise cancellation with microphones and counter-waves.

Instead, it relies on passive noise isolation with acoustic laminated glass and smart material choices.

A 16-speaker Harman Kardon system with A.R. Rahman-composed "sonic themes" enhances the experience.

The result is a refined, serene cabin built on solid engineering rather than electronic gimmicks.

What are your thoughts?

(via @j3vlogs_techinfo)
